tegies of plot development, language and composition, and production techniques that subverted the traditionally staged anthropomorphic gods.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aAnthropomorphism in literature. 0aGods, Greek, in literature. 4aAncient History & Classical Studies. 4aLiterary Studies.  aEuripides, revolution, plays, Greek gods, language, composition.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311066749308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2016z9783110485103oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2016z9783110485097oZDB-23-DGD40uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150170405540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501704055423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501704055/original  a978-3-11-066749-3  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGDb2016  aZDB-23-DGGb2016